Turkey Equity Movers: Garanti Bankasi, Karsan, Vakifbank Move

-- B y   B e n j a m i n   H a r v e y
-- 
2011-06-28T15:17:20Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-28/dogan-garanti-karsan-vakifbank-turkish-equity-preview.html
Turkey ’s benchmark  ISE National 100
Index (XU100)  rose 865.82, or 1.4 percent, to 62,819.08, the biggest
gain among major emerging market indexes as of the 5:30 p.m.
close in Istanbul  The following stocks were active. Symbols are in
parentheses.  Karsan Otomotiv Sanayii & Ticaret AS (KARSN TI) gained 5
kurus, or 3.1 percent, to 1.67 liras after Hyundai Motor Co.
said it agreed with the Turkish automaker to start assembling
Starex minivans and small buses starting in 2014.  Turkiye Garanti Bankasi AS (GARAN)  , Turkey’s largest
publicly listed lender, gained after JPMorgan Chase & Co. added
the stock to a regional model portfolio. JPMorgan said in a
report today that it raised Turkish equities back to “neutral”
after cutting them to “underweight” last week. The report
cited lower  oil prices  for upgrade. Garanti rose 18 kurus, or
2.5 percent, to 7.40 liras, its highest since June 10.  Turkiye Vakiflar Bankasi AS (VAKBN TI) was the other
Turkish bank added to JPMorgan’s regional model portfolio. The
shares jumped 14 kurus, or 4 percent, to 3.67 liras, their
biggest gain since April 4.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Benjamin Harvey in Istanbul at 
